This paper deals with the construction of neighborhood graphs for semi-supervised and relational models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the handling of multi-relational data, which is a topic often studied in the field of data management and databases. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves the use of inference and prediction, which are topics studied in the sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
